entries.name: Account
documentation: The full account information for a particular account ID.

entries.name: ExtrinsicCount
documentation: Total extrinsics count for the current block.

entries.name: BlockWeight
documentation: The current weight for the block.

entries.name: AllExtrinsicsLen
documentation: Total length (in bytes) for all extrinsics put together, for the current block.

entries.name: BlockHash
documentation: Map of block numbers to block hashes.

entries.name: ExtrinsicData
documentation: Extrinsics data for the current block (maps an extrinsic's index to its data).

entries.name: Number
documentation: The current block number being processed. Set by `execute_block`.

entries.name: ParentHash
documentation: Hash of the previous block.

entries.name: Digest
documentation: Digest of the current block, also part of the block header.

entries.name: Events
documentation: Events deposited for the current block.
NOTE: The item is unbound and should therefore never be read on chain.
It could otherwise inflate the PoV size of a block.
Events have a large in-memory size. Box the events to not go out-of-memory
just in case someone still reads them from within the runtime.

entries.name: EventCount
documentation: The number of events in the `Events<T>` list.

entries.name: EventTopics
documentation: Mapping between a topic (represented by T::Hash) and a vector of indexes
of events in the `<Events<T>>` list.
All topic vectors have deterministic storage locations depending on the topic. This
allows light-clients to leverage the changes trie storage tracking mechanism and
in case of changes fetch the list of events of interest.
The value has the type `(BlockNumberFor<T>, EventIndex)` because if we used only just
the `EventIndex` then in case if the topic has the same contents on the next block
no notification will be triggered thus the event might be lost.

entries.name: LastRuntimeUpgrade
documentation: Stores the `spec_version` and `spec_name` of when the last runtime upgrade happened.

entries.name: UpgradedToU32RefCount
documentation: True if we have upgraded so that `type RefCount` is `u32`. False (default) if not.

entries.name: UpgradedToTripleRefCount
documentation: True if we have upgraded so that AccountInfo contains three types of `RefCount`. False
(default) if not.

entries.name: ExecutionPhase
documentation: The execution phase of the block.

constants.name: BlockWeights
documentation: Block & extrinsics weights: base values and limits.

constants.name: BlockLength
documentation: The maximum length of a block (in bytes).

constants.name: BlockHashCount
documentation: Maximum number of block number to block hash mappings to keep (oldest pruned first).

constants.name: DbWeight
documentation: The weight of runtime database operations the runtime can invoke.

constants.name: Version
documentation: Get the chain's current version.

constants.name: SS58Prefix
documentation: The designated SS58 prefix of this chain.
This replaces the "ss58Format" property declared in the chain spec. Reason is
that the runtime should know about the prefix in order to make use of it as
an identifier of the chain.

constants.name: batched_calls_limit
documentation: The limit on the number of batched calls.

entries.name: Now
documentation: Current time for the current block.

entries.name: DidUpdate
documentation: Did the timestamp get updated in this block?

constants.name: MinimumPeriod
documentation: The minimum period between blocks. Beware that this is different to the *expected*
period that the block production apparatus provides. Your chosen consensus system will
generally work with this to determine a sensible block time. e.g. For Aura, it will be
double this period on default settings.

entries.name: IdentityOf
documentation: Information that is pertinent to identify the entity behind an account.
TWOX-NOTE: OK ― `AccountId` is a secure hash.

entries.name: SuperOf
documentation: The super-identity of an alternative "sub" identity together with its name, within that
context. If the account is not some other account's sub-identity, then just `None`.

entries.name: SubsOf
documentation: Alternative "sub" identities of this account.
The first item is the deposit, the second is a vector of the accounts.
TWOX-NOTE: OK ― `AccountId` is a secure hash.

entries.name: Registrars
documentation: The set of registrars. Not expected to get very big as can only be added through a
special origin (likely a council motion).
The index into this can be cast to `RegistrarIndex` to get a valid value.

constants.name: BasicDeposit
documentation: The amount held on deposit for a registered identity

constants.name: FieldDeposit
documentation: The amount held on deposit per additional field for a registered identity.

constants.name: SubAccountDeposit
documentation: The amount held on deposit for a registered subaccount. This should account for the fact
that one storage item's value will increase by the size of an account ID, and there will
be another trie item whose value is the size of an account ID plus 32 bytes.

constants.name: MaxSubAccounts
documentation: The maximum number of sub-accounts allowed per identified account.

constants.name: MaxAdditionalFields
documentation: Maximum number of additional fields that may be stored in an ID. Needed to bound the I/O
required to access an identity, but can be pretty high.

constants.name: MaxRegistrars
documentation: Maxmimum number of registrars allowed in the system. Needed to bound the complexity
of, e.g., updating judgements.

entries.name: Multisigs
documentation: The set of open multisig operations.

constants.name: DepositBase
documentation: The base amount of currency needed to reserve for creating a multisig execution or to
store a dispatch call for later.
This is held for an additional storage item whose value size is
`4 + sizeof((BlockNumber, Balance, AccountId))` bytes and whose key size is
`32 + sizeof(AccountId)` bytes.

constants.name: DepositFactor
documentation: The amount of currency needed per unit threshold when creating a multisig execution.
This is held for adding 32 bytes more into a pre-existing storage value.

constants.name: MaxSignatories
documentation: The maximum amount of signatories allowed in the multisig.

entries.name: PendingValidationCode
documentation: In case of a scheduled upgrade, this storage field contains the validation code to be applied.
As soon as the relay chain gives us the go-ahead signal, we will overwrite the [`:code`][sp_core::storage::well_known_keys::CODE]
which will result the next block process with the new validation code. This concludes the upgrade process.

entries.name: NewValidationCode
documentation: Validation code that is set by the parachain and is to be communicated to collator and
consequently the relay-chain.
This will be cleared in `on_initialize` of each new block if no other pallet already set
the value.

entries.name: ValidationData
documentation: The [`PersistedValidationData`] set for this block.
This value is expected to be set only once per block and it's never stored
in the trie.

entries.name: DidSetValidationCode
documentation: Were the validation data set to notify the relay chain?

entries.name: LastRelayChainBlockNumber
documentation: The relay chain block number associated with the last parachain block.

entries.name: UpgradeRestrictionSignal
documentation: An option which indicates if the relay-chain restricts signalling a validation code upgrade.
In other words, if this is `Some` and [`NewValidationCode`] is `Some` then the produced
candidate will be invalid.
This storage item is a mirror of the corresponding value for the current parachain from the
relay-chain. This value is ephemeral which means it doesn't hit the storage. This value is
set after the inherent.

entries.name: RelayStateProof
documentation: The state proof for the last relay parent block.
This field is meant to be updated each block with the validation data inherent. Therefore,
before processing of the inherent, e.g. in `on_initialize` this data may be stale.
This data is also absent from the genesis.

entries.name: RelevantMessagingState
documentation: The snapshot of some state related to messaging relevant to the current parachain as per
the relay parent.
This field is meant to be updated each block with the validation data inherent. Therefore,
before processing of the inherent, e.g. in `on_initialize` this data may be stale.
This data is also absent from the genesis.

entries.name: HostConfiguration
documentation: The parachain host configuration that was obtained from the relay parent.
This field is meant to be updated each block with the validation data inherent. Therefore,
before processing of the inherent, e.g. in `on_initialize` this data may be stale.
This data is also absent from the genesis.

entries.name: LastDmqMqcHead
documentation: The last downward message queue chain head we have observed.
This value is loaded before and saved after processing inbound downward messages carried
by the system inherent.

entries.name: LastHrmpMqcHeads
documentation: The message queue chain heads we have observed per each channel incoming channel.
This value is loaded before and saved after processing inbound downward messages carried
by the system inherent.

entries.name: ProcessedDownwardMessages
documentation: Number of downward messages processed in a block.
This will be cleared in `on_initialize` of each new block.

entries.name: HrmpWatermark
documentation: HRMP watermark that was set in a block.
This will be cleared in `on_initialize` of each new block.

entries.name: HrmpOutboundMessages
documentation: HRMP messages that were sent in a block.
This will be cleared in `on_initialize` of each new block.

entries.name: UpwardMessages
documentation: Upward messages that were sent in a block.
This will be cleared in `on_initialize` of each new block.

entries.name: PendingUpwardMessages
documentation: Upward messages that are still pending and not yet send to the relay chain.

entries.name: AnnouncedHrmpMessagesPerCandidate
documentation: The number of HRMP messages we observed in `on_initialize` and thus used that number for
announcing the weight of `on_initialize` and `on_finalize`.

entries.name: ReservedXcmpWeightOverride
documentation: The weight we reserve at the beginning of the block for processing XCMP messages. This
overrides the amount set in the Config trait.

entries.name: ReservedDmpWeightOverride
documentation: The weight we reserve at the beginning of the block for processing DMP messages. This
overrides the amount set in the Config trait.

entries.name: AuthorizedUpgrade
documentation: The next authorized upgrade, if there is one.

entries.name: CustomValidationHeadData
documentation: A custom head data that should be returned as result of `validate_block`.
See `Pallet::set_custom_validation_head_data` for more information.

entries.name: TotalIssuance
documentation: The total units issued in the system.

entries.name: InactiveIssuance
documentation: The total units of outstanding deactivated balance in the system.

entries.name: Account
documentation: The Balances pallet example of storing the balance of an account.
# Example
```nocompile
impl pallet_balances::Config for Runtime {
type AccountStore = StorageMapShim<Self::Account<Runtime>, frame_system::Provider<Runtime>, AccountId, Self::AccountData<Balance>>
You can also store the balance of an account in the `System` pallet.
# Example
```nocompile
impl pallet_balances::Config for Runtime {
type AccountStore = System
But this comes with tradeoffs, storing account balances in the system pallet stores
`frame_system` data alongside the account data contrary to storing account balances in the
`Balances` pallet, which uses a `StorageMap` to store balances data only.
NOTE: This is only used in the case that this pallet is used to store balances.

entries.name: Locks
documentation: Any liquidity locks on some account balances.
NOTE: Should only be accessed when setting, changing and freeing a lock.

entries.name: Reserves
documentation: Named reserves on some account balances.

entries.name: Holds
documentation: Holds on account balances.

entries.name: Freezes
documentation: Freeze locks on account balances.

constants.name: ExistentialDeposit
documentation: The minimum amount required to keep an account open. MUST BE GREATER THAN ZERO!
If you *really* need it to be zero, you can enable the feature `insecure_zero_ed` for
this pallet. However, you do so at your own risk: this will open up a major DoS vector.
In case you have multiple sources of provider references, you may also get unexpected
behaviour if you set this to zero.
Bottom line: Do yourself a favour and make it at least one!

constants.name: MaxLocks
documentation: The maximum number of locks that should exist on an account.
Not strictly enforced, but used for weight estimation.

constants.name: MaxReserves
documentation: The maximum number of named reserves that can exist on an account.

constants.name: MaxHolds
documentation: The maximum number of holds that can exist on an account at any time.

constants.name: MaxFreezes
documentation: The maximum number of individual freeze locks that can exist on an account at any time.

constants.name: OperationalFeeMultiplier
documentation: A fee mulitplier for `Operational` extrinsics to compute "virtual tip" to boost their
`priority`
This value is multipled by the `final_fee` to obtain a "virtual tip" that is later
added to a tip component in regular `priority` calculations.
It means that a `Normal` transaction can front-run a similarly-sized `Operational`
extrinsic (with no tip), by including a tip value greater than the virtual tip.
```rust,ignore
// For `Normal`
let priority = priority_calc(tip);
// For `Operational`
let virtual_tip = (inclusion_fee + tip) * OperationalFeeMultiplier;
let priority = priority_calc(tip + virtual_tip);
Note that since we use `final_fee` the multiplier applies also to the regular `tip`
sent with the transaction. So, not only does the transaction get a priority bump based
on the `inclusion_fee`, but we also amplify the impact of tips applied to `Operational`
transactions.

entries.name: Vesting
documentation: Information regarding the vesting of a given account.

entries.name: StorageVersion
documentation: Storage version of the pallet.
New networks start with latest version, as determined by the genesis build.

constants.name: MinVestedTransfer
documentation: The minimum amount transferred to call `vested_transfer`.

entries.name: Asset
documentation: Details of an asset.

entries.name: Account
documentation: The holdings of a specific account for a specific asset.

entries.name: Approvals
documentation: Approved balance transfers. First balance is the amount approved for transfer. Second
is the amount of `T::Currency` reserved for storing this.
First key is the asset ID, second key is the owner and third key is the delegate.

entries.name: Metadata
documentation: Metadata of an asset.

constants.name: RemoveItemsLimit
documentation: Max number of items to destroy per `destroy_accounts` and `destroy_approvals` call.
Must be configured to result in a weight that makes each call fit in a block.

constants.name: AssetDeposit
documentation: The basic amount of funds that must be reserved for an asset.

constants.name: AssetAccountDeposit
documentation: The amount of funds that must be reserved for a non-provider asset account to be
maintained.

constants.name: MetadataDepositBase
documentation: The basic amount of funds that must be reserved when adding metadata to your asset.

constants.name: MetadataDepositPerByte
documentation: The additional funds that must be reserved for the number of bytes you store in your
metadata.

constants.name: ApprovalDeposit
documentation: The amount of funds that must be reserved when creating a new approval.

constants.name: StringLimit
documentation: The maximum length of a name or symbol stored on-chain.

entries.name: ProposalCount
documentation: Number of proposals that have been made.

entries.name: Proposals
documentation: Proposals that have been made.

entries.name: Deactivated
documentation: The amount which has been reported as inactive to Currency.

entries.name: Approvals
documentation: Proposal indices that have been approved but not yet awarded.

constants.name: ProposalBond
documentation: Fraction of a proposal's value that should be bonded in order to place the proposal.
An accepted proposal gets these back. A rejected proposal does not.

constants.name: ProposalBondMinimum
documentation: Minimum amount of funds that should be placed in a deposit for making a proposal.

constants.name: ProposalBondMaximum
documentation: Maximum amount of funds that should be placed in a deposit for making a proposal.

constants.name: SpendPeriod
documentation: Period between successive spends.

constants.name: Burn
documentation: Percentage of spare funds (if any) that are burnt per spend period.

constants.name: PalletId
documentation: The treasury's pallet id, used for deriving its sovereign account ID.

constants.name: MaxApprovals
documentation: The maximum number of approvals that can wait in the spending queue.
NOTE: This parameter is also used within the Bounties Pallet extension if enabled.

entries.name: Agenda
documentation: Items to be executed, indexed by the block number that they should be executed on.

entries.name: Lookup
documentation: Lookup from a name to the block number and index of the task.
For v3 -> v4 the previously unbounded identities are Blake2-256 hashed to form the v4
identities.

constants.name: MaximumWeight
documentation: The maximum weight that may be scheduled per block for any dispatchables.

constants.name: MaxScheduledPerBlock
documentation: The maximum number of scheduled calls in the queue for a single block.
NOTE:
+ Dependent pallets' benchmarks might require a higher limit for the setting. Set a
higher limit under `runtime-benchmarks` feature.

entries.name: Proposals
documentation: The hashes of the active proposals.

entries.name: ProposalOf
documentation: Actual proposal for a given hash, if it's current.

entries.name: Voting
documentation: Votes on a given proposal, if it is ongoing.

entries.name: ProposalCount
documentation: Proposals so far.

entries.name: Members
documentation: The current members of the collective. This is stored sorted (just by value).

entries.name: Prime
documentation: The prime member that helps determine the default vote behavior in case of absentations.

constants.name: MaxProposalWeight
documentation: The maximum weight of a dispatch call that can be proposed and executed.

entries.name: Members
documentation: The current membership, stored as an ordered Vec.

entries.name: Prime
documentation: The current prime member, if one exists.

entries.name: PublicPropCount
documentation: The number of (public) proposals that have been made so far.

entries.name: PublicProps
documentation: The public proposals. Unsorted. The second item is the proposal.

entries.name: DepositOf
documentation: Those who have locked a deposit.
TWOX-NOTE: Safe, as increasing integer keys are safe.

entries.name: ReferendumCount
documentation: The next free referendum index, aka the number of referenda started so far.

entries.name: LowestUnbaked
documentation: The lowest referendum index representing an unbaked referendum. Equal to
`ReferendumCount` if there isn't a unbaked referendum.

entries.name: ReferendumInfoOf
documentation: Information concerning any given referendum.
TWOX-NOTE: SAFE as indexes are not under an attacker’s control.

entries.name: VotingOf
documentation: All votes for a particular voter. We store the balance for the number of votes that we
have recorded. The second item is the total amount of delegations, that will be added.
TWOX-NOTE: SAFE as `AccountId`s are crypto hashes anyway.

entries.name: LastTabledWasExternal
documentation: True if the last referendum tabled was submitted externally. False if it was a public
proposal.

entries.name: NextExternal
documentation: The referendum to be tabled whenever it would be valid to table an external proposal.
This happens when a referendum needs to be tabled and one of two conditions are met:
- `LastTabledWasExternal` is `false`; or
- `PublicProps` is empty.

entries.name: Blacklist
documentation: A record of who vetoed what. Maps proposal hash to a possible existent block number
(until when it may not be resubmitted) and who vetoed it.

entries.name: Cancellations
documentation: Record of all proposals that have been subject to emergency cancellation.

entries.name: MetadataOf
documentation: General information concerning any proposal or referendum.
The `PreimageHash` refers to the preimage of the `Preimages` provider which can be a JSON
dump or IPFS hash of a JSON file.
Consider a garbage collection for a metadata of finished referendums to `unrequest` (remove)
large preimages.

constants.name: EnactmentPeriod
documentation: The period between a proposal being approved and enacted.
It should generally be a little more than the unstake period to ensure that
voting stakers have an opportunity to remove themselves from the system in the case
where they are on the losing side of a vote.

constants.name: LaunchPeriod
documentation: How often (in blocks) new public referenda are launched.

constants.name: VotingPeriod
documentation: How often (in blocks) to check for new votes.

constants.name: VoteLockingPeriod
documentation: The minimum period of vote locking.
It should be no shorter than enactment period to ensure that in the case of an approval,
those successful voters are locked into the consequences that their votes entail.

constants.name: MinimumDeposit
documentation: The minimum amount to be used as a deposit for a public referendum proposal.

constants.name: InstantAllowed
documentation: Indicator for whether an emergency origin is even allowed to happen. Some chains may
want to set this permanently to `false`, others may want to condition it on things such
as an upgrade having happened recently.

constants.name: FastTrackVotingPeriod
documentation: Minimum voting period allowed for a fast-track referendum.

constants.name: CooloffPeriod
documentation: Period in blocks where an external proposal may not be re-submitted after being vetoed.

constants.name: MaxVotes
documentation: The maximum number of votes for an account.
Also used to compute weight, an overly big value can
lead to extrinsic with very big weight: see `delegate` for instance.

constants.name: MaxProposals
documentation: The maximum number of public proposals that can exist at any time.

constants.name: MaxDeposits
documentation: The maximum number of deposits a public proposal may have at any time.

constants.name: MaxBlacklisted
documentation: The maximum number of items which can be blacklisted.

entries.name: StatusFor
documentation: The request status of a given hash.

entries.name: DatalogIndex
documentation: Ringbuffer start/end pointers

entries.name: DatalogItem
documentation: Ringbuffer items

constants.name: WindowSize
documentation: Data log window size

entries.name: Total
documentation: Total count of registered digital twins.

entries.name: Owner
documentation: Get owner of digital twin with given id.

entries.name: DigitalTwin
documentation: Get internal structure of difital twin in format: topic hash -> source account.

entries.name: Oracle
documentation: The `AccountId` of Ethereum RWS oracle.

entries.name: Ledger
documentation: RWS subscriptions storage.

entries.name: Devices
documentation: Subscription linked devices.

entries.name: AuctionQueue
documentation: Ongoing subscription auctions.

entries.name: AuctionNext
documentation: Next auction index.

entries.name: Auction
documentation: Indexed auction ledger.

entries.name: UnspendBondValue
documentation: This is intermediate value used to escape bonded value loss.
For each bond if value is not enough to issue new subscription then bonded value will
be written here.

constants.name: ReferenceCallWeight
documentation: Reference call weight, general transaction consumes this weight.

constants.name: AuctionDuration
documentation: Subscription auction duration in blocks.

constants.name: AuctionCost
documentation: How much token should be bonded to launch new auction.

constants.name: MinimalBid
documentation: Minimal auction bid.

entries.name: NextIndex
documentation: Next liability index.

entries.name: AgreementOf
documentation: Technical and economical parameters of liability.

entries.name: ReportOf
documentation: Result of liability execution.

entries.name: Lighthouse
documentation: Current block lighthouse account.

constants.name: BlockReward
documentation: Reward amount for block proposer.

entries.name: InboundXcmpStatus
documentation: Status of the inbound XCMP channels.

entries.name: InboundXcmpMessages
documentation: Inbound aggregate XCMP messages. It can only be one per ParaId/block.

entries.name: OutboundXcmpStatus
documentation: The non-empty XCMP channels in order of becoming non-empty, and the index of the first
and last outbound message. If the two indices are equal, then it indicates an empty
queue and there must be a non-`Ok` `OutboundStatus`. We assume queues grow no greater
than 65535 items. Queue indices for normal messages begin at one; zero is reserved in
case of the need to send a high-priority signal message this block.
The bool is true if there is a signal message waiting to be sent.

entries.name: OutboundXcmpMessages
documentation: The messages outbound in a given XCMP channel.

entries.name: SignalMessages
documentation: Any signal messages waiting to be sent.

entries.name: QueueConfig
documentation: The configuration which controls the dynamics of the outbound queue.

entries.name: Overweight
documentation: The messages that exceeded max individual message weight budget.
These message stay in this storage map until they are manually dispatched via
`service_overweight`.

entries.name: CounterForOverweight
documentation: Counter for the related counted storage map

entries.name: OverweightCount
documentation: The number of overweight messages ever recorded in `Overweight`. Also doubles as the next
available free overweight index.

entries.name: QueueSuspended
documentation: Whether or not the XCMP queue is suspended from executing incoming XCMs or not.

entries.name: QueryCounter
documentation: The latest available query index.

entries.name: Queries
documentation: The ongoing queries.

entries.name: AssetTraps
documentation: The existing asset traps.
Key is the blake2 256 hash of (origin, versioned `MultiAssets`) pair. Value is the number of
times this pair has been trapped (usually just 1 if it exists at all).

entries.name: SafeXcmVersion
documentation: Default version to encode XCM when latest version of destination is unknown. If `None`,
then the destinations whose XCM version is unknown are considered unreachable.

entries.name: SupportedVersion
documentation: The Latest versions that we know various locations support.

entries.name: VersionNotifiers
documentation: All locations that we have requested version notifications from.

entries.name: VersionNotifyTargets
documentation: The target locations that are subscribed to our version changes, as well as the most recent
of our versions we informed them of.

entries.name: VersionDiscoveryQueue
documentation: Destinations whose latest XCM version we would like to know. Duplicates not allowed, and
the `u32` counter is the number of times that a send to the destination has been attempted,
which is used as a prioritization.

entries.name: CurrentMigration
documentation: The current migration's stage, if any.

entries.name: RemoteLockedFungibles
documentation: Fungible assets which we know are locked on a remote chain.

entries.name: LockedFungibles
documentation: Fungible assets which we know are locked on this chain.

entries.name: XcmExecutionSuspended
documentation: Global suspension state of the XCM executor.

entries.name: Configuration
documentation: The configuration.

entries.name: PageIndex
documentation: The page index.

entries.name: Pages
documentation: The queue pages.

entries.name: Overweight
documentation: The overweight messages.

entries.name: CounterForOverweight
documentation: Counter for the related counted storage map
